# Entities
- Script { id, version, content, durationMins, elements: ProductionElementID[], scenes: SceneID[], syncedModules: ModuleKey[] }
- Scene { id, number, slug, heading, locationType: "INT"|"EXT", timeOfDay, contentRange, durationMins, elementIds: ProductionElementID[] }
- ProductionElement { id, type, name, category, linkedScenes: SceneID[], linkedActorId?, customFields, estCost? } 
  - element `type` follows SB-style 30+ taxonomy.
  - `linkedActorId` enables Celtx-style characterâ†’actor mapping.
- Actor { id, name, role?, contactId? }
- Contact { id, name, department, role, phone?, email?, notes? }
- Location { id, name, address?, mapUrl?, photos[], permits[], notes }
- StripDay { id, date?, scenes: SceneID[], durationMinsTotal }
- BudgetLineItem { id, scope: "scene"|"element"|"day"|"project", refId, description, qty, unitCost, total, currency }

# Notes
- All monetary values use Decimal (no float). Provide adapters/helpers.
- Computed fields (e.g., day totals) live in selectors/hooks, not stored redundantly.